The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for identifying elephants in the wild, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of support vector machine classification and off-the-shelf CNN features also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Additionally, the use of multiple images to deal with occlusion and varying viewpoints suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) techniques.
